(3. Process Frame: "There is a simple path.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 705.50 Tm
(People relax when they know the map. Tell them what will happen before it happens. This reduces) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 692.10 Tm
(surprise and prevents them from interrupting with questions at the wrong time.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 671.70 Tm
("I will keep this simple. First I check the energy usage and equipment, then I explain the program,) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 658.70 Tm
(then we compare numbers. If it makes sense, we talk next steps. If it does not, no pressure.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 632.70 Tm
(4. Qualification Frame: "The program must approve the home; I do not decide by) Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 617.20 Tm
(opinion.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 596.70 Tm
(This frame protects trust. You are not begging them to buy. You are helping determine fit.) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 583.30 Tm
(Qualification also makes the conversation feel like an evaluation instead of a pitch.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 562.90 Tm
("The application and home details determine what is possible. My job is to help you understand the) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 549.90 Tm
(option and see if you qualify.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 523.90 Tm
(5. Utility Frame: "Doing nothing is still a decision.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 503.40 Tm
(The central reframe in solar is that staying with the utility is not neutral. It is an ongoing) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 490.00 Tm
(payment path. You must make the current path visible without exaggeration.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 469.60 Tm
("The current option is simple: keep paying the utility with no fixed end date. The only question is) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 456.60 Tm
(whether there is a better option for this house.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 430.60 Tm
(6. Ownership Frame: "Renting power versus controlling more of it.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 410.10 Tm
(Homeowners understand ownership. Connect the energy decision to the same logic that made them buy a) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 396.70 Tm
(home instead of rent, while staying accurate about financing, equipment, and program terms.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 376.30 Tm
("You bought the home because ownership gave you more control. Energy is similar: the question is) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 363.30 Tm
(whether it makes sense to keep renting power every month or move toward more control.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 337.30 Tm
(7. Discovery Frame: "Concerns are welcome.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 316.80 Tm
(Most salespeople fear objections. Masters invite them. The frame is: concerns do not block the) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 303.40 Tm
(close; hidden concerns block the close. If the homeowner trusts you enough to object, the deal is) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 290.00 Tm
(still alive.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 269.60 Tm
("I actually want every concern on the table. It is easier to make a good decision when nothing is) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 256.60 Tm
(hiding in the background.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 230.60 Tm
