/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 719.00 Tm
(Reframing Common Solar Objections) Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 687.00 Tm
(Objection: "I need to think about it.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 666.50 Tm
(Do not attack this. Thinking is reasonable. The reframe is that thinking usually means there is an) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 653.10 Tm
(unresolved question, unclear comparison, or emotional discomfort.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 632.70 Tm
(Weak response: "What is there to think about?") Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 611.70 Tm
(Master response: "Of course. Usually when someone says that, it means one part is still unclear. Is) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 598.70 Tm
(it the price, the contract, the roof, the timeline, or just the idea of making the decision today?") Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 577.70 Tm
(Advance: "If we clear that part up and the numbers still make sense, would you be comfortable taking) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 564.70 Tm
(the next step?") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 538.70 Tm
(Objection: "It is too expensive.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 518.20 Tm
(Expensive compared to what? That is the key. Never let price float alone in the air. Anchor it to) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 504.80 Tm
(the current utility cost and future uncertainty.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 484.40 Tm
("I understand. Let us compare it to what you are already paying. If solar is higher, we should not do) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 471.40 Tm
(it. If it is lower and more predictable, then it is not an added expense; it is a replacement) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 458.40 Tm
(option.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 432.40 Tm
(Objection: "I do not want another bill.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 411.90 Tm
(This is often the cleanest reframe in the entire sale.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 391.50 Tm
("I agree. Nobody wants another bill. The goal is not to add one. The goal is to reduce or replace the) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 378.50 Tm
(one you already have with a better structure, if you qualify.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 352.50 Tm
(Objection: "Just send me information.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 332.00 Tm
(This usually means the homeowner wants distance from pressure. Reframe information as something that) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 318.60 Tm
(only becomes useful after you know their numbers.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 298.20 Tm
("I can send information, but generic information will not tell you whether your home qualifies or) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 285.20 Tm
(whether the numbers are lower. Let us finish the comparison first, then I can send you the exact) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 272.20 Tm
(summary.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 246.20 Tm
(Objection: "I want to get more quotes.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 225.70 Tm
(Do not insult shopping. Reframe it around comparing the right things.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 205.30 Tm
("That is smart. If you compare, make sure you compare the same equipment class, warranty, production) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 192.30 Tm
(estimate, financing terms, dealer fees, roof work, utility process, and monthly outcome. If you only) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 179.30 Tm
(compare the headline price, it can be misleading.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 153.30 Tm
(Objection: "My spouse is not here.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 132.80 Tm
(Never minimize the missing decision-maker. Reframe the current conversation as preparation, not) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 119.40 Tm
(exclusion.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 99.00 Tm
("That makes sense. A decision like this should include both of you. Let us make sure you understand) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 86.00 Tm
(the option clearly, then we can either bring them in by phone or schedule a time when you are both) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 73.00 Tm
(present.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 282.00 30.00 Tm
