/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 731.00 Tm
("That is completely your choice. The reason it comes up is that financing approval determines the) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 718.00 Tm
(exact option. We only do it with your permission, and I can explain what kind of check it is before) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 705.00 Tm
(anything happens.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 679.00 Tm
(Objection: "Rates might change later.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 658.50 Tm
(Reframe uncertainty both ways. Utility rates can change, program terms can change, and assumptions) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 645.10 Tm
(should be clear.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 624.70 Tm
("True. That is why we compare what is known today and use conservative assumptions. The question is) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 611.70 Tm
(which path gives you more predictability.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 585.70 Tm
(Objection: "I want to wait.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 565.20 Tm
(Waiting feels safe because it avoids action. Reframe by naming the cost of waiting without fake) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 551.80 Tm
(urgency.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 531.40 Tm
("Waiting is an option. The only thing I would compare is what waiting costs if your utility bill) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 518.40 Tm
(continues and the current program terms change. If waiting still makes more sense after that, then) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 505.40 Tm
(waiting is the right call.") Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 472.40 Tm
(Advanced Reframes by Emotional State) Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 440.40 Tm
(When the homeowner is confused) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 419.90 Tm
(Confusion is not a no. It is a request for structure. Slow down and create a map.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 399.50 Tm
("Let me simplify this. There are only three things to understand: what you pay now, what the solar) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 386.50 Tm
(option would be, and what has to happen for the system to turn on.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 360.50 Tm
(When the homeowner is defensive) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 340.00 Tm
(Defensiveness usually means they feel sold, judged, or trapped. Rebuild safety.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 319.60 Tm
("I may have moved too fast. Let us pause. My job is not to push you; it is to make sure you) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 306.60 Tm
(understand the option.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 280.60 Tm
(When the homeowner is skeptical) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 260.10 Tm
(Skepticism can be healthy. Reframe it as good decision-making.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 239.70 Tm
("I like that you are asking that. The people who ask detailed questions usually make the best) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 226.70 Tm
(decisions.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 200.70 Tm
(When the homeowner is excited) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 180.20 Tm
(Excitement can close, but it can also create later remorse if details are skipped. Reframe) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 166.80 Tm
(excitement into informed confidence.) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 146.40 Tm
("I am glad you like the idea. Let us still walk through the important details so you feel good about) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 133.40 Tm
(it tomorrow too.") Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 107.40 Tm
(When the homeowner is silent) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 86.90 Tm
