/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 731.00 Tm
("The utility is not evil. It is just the current system. You pay every month, the rate can change,) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 718.00 Tm
(and there is no ownership at the end. Solar is worth checking because it may give you a lower and) Tj
/F3 9.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 705.00 Tm
(more predictable structure.") Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 685.00 Tm
(This is cleaner than saying, "The utility is robbing you." Strong framers do not need cartoon) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 671.60 Tm
(villains. They make the math visible.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 639.20 Tm
(How to Frame Credibility) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 613.20 Tm
(Credibility should be casual, verified, and relevant. If you overdo credibility, it sounds like a) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 599.80 Tm
(pitch. If you underdo it, the homeowner may not understand that solar is mainstream.) Tj
/F2 11.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 574.40 Tm
(The credibility triangle) Tj
/F1 9.8 Tf
1 0 0 1 66.00 554.90 Tm
